<br>
As stated, so minimal it's bearly measurable, and certainly not 10 points.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> , but I don't really use regen on raids<br>
....<br>
Right now we are camping West Wing ToV  <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Urm.. So if a fight against an AoE'ing mob that lasts 3 minutes, and you regen 15 * 10 * 3 = 450 Hp.. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> every fight</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> your not using it ?<br>
<br>
Exactly how many times do you think you will get to click your BP during a fight without AoE disrupting casting... and stopping attacking to do so ? <br>
<br>
After a fight.. well, your pulling.. No time to click it.<br>
<br>
And if your not pulling, the fact that bandages, and FA3 &amp; Fungi skill will get you to 100% HP's just as fast as clicking the BP.<br>
<br>
And finally. That leader BP could go to a druid. Who then has mana free Regrowth of the Grove.. which he casts on you, adding another 15 HP regen per tick.<br>
<br>
I think it's clear which it &quot;better&quot;. <p><br>
